               <desc type="building-data" xml:lang="en">
                  <p source="#bibl000209-1" xml:lang="en">Tianwang Hall is the first major wooden structure on the central axis of the <placeName ref="/keyword/000064">Longxing Monastery</placeName> complex. Since there is no mountain gate in monastery, Tianwang Hall plays the role of the main entrance of Longxing Temple (河北省正定縣文物保管所 2000, 3). The creation year of this hall was not recorded in the literature, but it can be inferred to be a <term ref="/keyword/k000074">Northern Song dynasty</term> building based on its framework and bracket features. The hall is five bays or 23.28 meters wide, two bays or 9.62 meters deep, with a single-eave green glazed tile hip-and-gable (<term subtype="keyword" ref="/keyword/k000143">xieshan 歇山</term>) roof. The total building area is about 380 square meters. The column heads are decorated with five-fold double-stolen center construction (<term ref="/keyword/k000024">touxinzao 偷心造</term>) brackets. The brackets of Tianwang Hall underwent additions and modifications in the 45th year of Qianlong reign in the <term ref="/keyword/k000070">Qing dynasty</term> (1780), when the first step of the <term ref="/keyword/k000074">Song dynasty</term> column head layout was changed and intercolumnar bracket sets (<term ref="/keyword/k000105">補間鋪作</term>) were added (<term>pingshenke 平身科</term>).</p>
                  <p source="#bibl000209-1" xml:lang="zh-Hant">天王殿為<placeName ref="/keyword/000064">隆興寺</placeName>中軸線上第一座主要木構建築。因隆興寺未設山門，天王殿起到了隆興寺大門入口的作用 (河北省正定縣文物保管所 2000，3)。此殿的創建年代未被文字資料記載，但根據架構以及斗栱特征可推斷其為<term ref="/keyword/k000074">北宋</term>建築。該殿面闊五間，寬23.28米，進深兩間，深9.62米，為單檐<term subtype="keyword" ref="/keyword/k000143">歇山</term>綠琉璃瓦剪邊頂。總建築面積約為380平方米。柱頭施五鋪作雙抄<term ref="/keyword/k000024">偷心造</term><term>斗栱</term>。天王殿的斗栱在<term ref="/keyword/k000070">清</term>乾隆四十五年（1780）經歷了增補修改，改製了<term ref="/keyword/k000074">宋朝</term>柱頭鋪作原構的第一跳<term ref="/keyword/k000172">華栱</term>，並在柱間添加了<term ref="/keyword/k000105">補間鋪作</term>（<term>平身科</term>）。</p>
               </desc>
